{
  "answer": "**The precise opening verse (matla, or first couplet) of Chapter 1 of *Diwan-e-Ghalib* (\"Aa ke meri jaan ko qarar nahin hai\") is:**\n\nآ کہ مری جان کو قرار نہیں ہے  \nطاقتِ بیدادِ انتظار نہیں ہے[^1]\n\nThis is the first sher (couplet) of the ghazal, as presented in the original Urdu (Arabic script) variant.[^1]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nAa ke meri jaan ko qarar nahin hai  \nTaaqat-e-bidaad-e-intezar nahin hai[^2]\n\n**English translation:**  \nMy soul is free from comfort, free from care,  \nThe strength to face this wait of deep despair is not there.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/01-aa-ke-meri-jaan-ko-qarar-nahin-hai/original/#p-8d955a).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/01-aa-ke-meri-jaan-ko-qarar-nahin-hai/transliteration/#p-8d955a).\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/01-aa-ke-meri-jaan-ko-qarar-nahin-hai/translation/#p-8c8b08).",
